Package specific

Class StoreState

java.lang.Object
java.util.Observable
general.State
specific.StoreState
public class StoreState extends State
Represents the state of the store during the simulation, including time management, customer queue management, and keeping track of various statistics such as missed customers, paid customers, and total queue time. This class is responsible for initializing the simulation settings based on input parameters and updating the state as events occur.

  • Constructor Details

    • StoreState

      public StoreState(double lambda, int seed, float closeStoreTime, int checkoutsOpen, int maxCapacityInStore, double minPayTime, double maxPayTime, double minPickTime, double maxPickTime, boolean print)
      Constructs a StoreState with specified simulation parameters. Initializes random streams for pick and pay times using provided min/max values and seed.
      Parameters:
      lambda - The average arrival rate of customers.
      seed - The seed for random number generation to ensure reproducibility.
      closeStoreTime - The time at which the store closes and no more customers are allowed to enter.
      checkoutsOpen - The number of checkouts open for processing payments.
      maxCapacityInStore - The maximum number of customers allowed in the store at one time.
      minPayTime - The minimum time it takes for a customer to pay.
      maxPayTime - The maximum time it takes for a customer to pay.
      minPickTime - The minimum time it takes for a customer to pick their items.
      maxPickTime - The maximum time it takes for a customer to pick their items.
      print - The state of whether the state should be printed or not.
